This product credits external patterns:

- Microsoft Chat Customizations Evaluations — anti-injection wrapping
  (<PROMPT_TO_CLASSIFY> tags), extractJSON utility, parallel pipeline,
  size limits, diagnostic output conventions.

- claude-code-router (musistudio/claude-code-router) — the CCR scenario
  protocol shape (background / think / longContext / webSearch / image)
  informed Maestro's turn-type classifier design even though Maestro does
  not depend on or interoperate with CCR at runtime.

- RTK (Rust Token Killer) — hook-based token compression pattern;
  Maestro complements RTK by operating at the model-selection layer
  while RTK operates at the tool-output layer.

- PostHog — telemetry consent pattern (deferred to v0.3).
